HEADWORD: Demonize
<hw>De"mon*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Demonized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Demonizing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. LL.
<ets>daemonizare</ets> to be possessed by a demon, Gr.
<grk>dai`mwn</grk>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To convert into a demon; to
infuse the principles or fury of a demon into.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To control or possess by a demon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Demonocracy</ent>⟦br⟧
